Dear Trustees,


We hope this finds you well. Further to previous communication:


Maintenance
Fire safety - Vaal Triangle Fire Services<http://www.vaaltrianglefireservic=
es.co.za/> located nearby will provide us with a quote for any requirements=
 and issue the statutory certificate. Please confirm who will be the contac=
t person for the inspector to conduct a survey (would Monday be fine)?

Common Property - Please also advise if there are any maintenance, repair o=
r replacement needs that we can source quotes for?


Financial

Statutory audit - Please advise if there is an auditor you would appoint to=
 complete the annual financial statements and audit. Alternatively, we can =
suggest Certified Master Auditors (CMA<http://www.cmaauditors.co.za>).


Management Report - Please find attached for a detailed analysis of Transva=
lia's financial performance as at 31 May 2019. Includes Owner Age Analysis =
report of levies outstanding.


Budget - Please see attached the estimate budget and proposed levy schedule=
 for 2020. Monthly municipal charges are based on past billing and we are i=
nvestigating the amounts with Emfuleni. We will report back on this shortly=
. In the meantime, please would someone be able to provide us with a copy o=
f your prepaid electricity receipt / advise us on the provider?


Arrears

CSOS - After intensively pursuing the CSOS route for owners in arrears sinc=
e February, those with conciliation hearings did not attend and so cases we=
re to go to adjudication. CSOS then informed us that their Adjudication uni=
t is undergoing transitional changes and the Adjudication process will foll=
ow in due course (up to 2-months). It has become apparent that CSOS is unab=
le to expeditiously resolve these cases.


Legal - No debtors have adhered to their payment arrangements or signed Ack=
nowledgment of Debt. The decision has therefore been made to hand over the =
following units to BBM Law who specialise in arrear levy collections:

  *   TV2 (Mphiyakhe) - will not increase payment; balance outstanding incr=
easing.
  *   TV3 (Bahyi) - paid minimal amounts then nothing since Jan; not respon=
ding to contact efforts.
  *   TV5 (Fick) - unable to contact; no payments on record.
  *   TV9 & TV13 (Motsoagae) - making monthly payments of R750 for each uni=
t; arrears increasing; not responding to contact efforts.
  *   TV15 (Alemeida / Da Silva) - Monthly payments of R2,000 does not cove=
r levies and charges; needs to increase payment amount; unable to contact.

In brief, a (registered) Letter of Demand will now be sent / served by the =
Sheriff. If no response from the debtors, a formal Summons will be issued a=
nd served again by the Sheriff. If owners do not defend, we will apply for =
Default Judgement which vastly affects the creditworthiness of the debtor. =
It is at this stage that debtors are most likely to adhere to formal paymen=
t arrangements to avoid Warrants of Execution where movable assets are sold=
 in auction. However, the final stage would be Section 66 where the propert=
y is sold to recover the debt owed to the BC.


We look forward to your feedback and suggestions to address the above manag=
ement issues.


Kind regards,

Nancy

